@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction

Master of Ceremonies üé§ is a collection of tools for presenting.  Use it to configure Emacs for live demonstrations and presentations.  It can also be used to author content for richer presentations.

@itemize
@item
üéõÔ∏è @code{moc-dispatch}  is a collection of tools to quickly configure a frame for screen sharing or presenting on a projector.

@item
üîé @code{moc-focus} is a tool to create@comma{} both live and pre-recorded@comma{} illustrations of code and other text in Emacs.
@end itemize

@node Authoring üñãÔ∏è
@chapter Authoring üñãÔ∏è

@code{moc-focus} is very powerful for pre-recording sequences of images to build up larger expressions for the audience@comma{} highlighting key points in the content.

Several workflows are supported:
@itemize
@item
üé¨ @strong{live presentation}: focus some text and use the cursor and highlights to point out key parts of the contents
@item
‚ñ∂Ô∏è @strong{persisted playback}: save focused text and all configured highlights@comma{} perhaps to use as a sequence of steps in a @ref{Top,dslide,,dslide,} presentation.
@item
üì∏ @strong{saving screenshots}: save screenshots for use in external applications such as Blender or another video authoring tool.
@end itemize

